verses.text_plain: Woe is me! for I am as when they have gathered the summer fruits, as the grapegleanings of the vintage: there is no cluster to eat: my soul desired the firstripe fruit.
verses.verse_html:
1Woe is me! for I am as when they have gathered the summer fruits, as the grapegleanings of the vintage: there is no cluster to eat: my soul desired the firstripe fruit. ▼
▼ when…: Heb. the gatherings of summer

tokens.text: is me! for I am as when they have gathered

footnotes.body_text: ▼ when…: Heb. the gatherings of summer
footnotes.body_html: ▼ when…: Heb. the gatherings of summer

verses.text_plain: The good man is perished out of the earth: and there is none upright among men: they all lie in wait for blood; they hunt every man his brother with a net.
verses.verse_html:
2The good man is perished out of the earth: and there is none upright among men: they all lie in wait for blood; they hunt every man his brother with a net. ▼
▼ good: or, godly, or, merciful

footnotes.body_html: ▼ good: or, godly, or, merciful

verses.text_plain: That they may do evil with both hands earnestly, the prince asketh, and the judge asketh for a reward; and the great man, he uttereth his mischievous desire: so they wrap it up.
verses.verse_html:
3That they may do evil with both hands earnestly, the prince asketh, and the judge asketh for a reward; and the great man, he uttereth his mischievous desire: so they wrap it up. ▼
▼ his…: Heb. the mischief of his soul

footnotes.body_text: ▼ his…: Heb. the mischief of his soul
footnotes.body_html: ▼ his…: Heb. the mischief of his soul

verses.text_plain: The best of them is as a brier: the most upright is sharper than a thorn hedge: the day of thy watchmen and thy visitation cometh; now shall be their perplexity.
verses.verse_html: 4The best of them is as a brier: the most upright is sharper than a thorn hedge: the day of thy watchmen and thy visitation cometh; now shall be their perplexity.

verses.text_plain: Trust ye not in a friend, put ye not confidence in a guide: keep the doors of thy mouth from her that lieth in thy bosom.
verses.verse_html: 5Trust ye not in a friend, put ye not confidence in a guide: keep the doors of thy mouth from her that lieth in thy bosom.

verses.text_plain: For the son dishonoureth the father, the daughter riseth up against her mother, the daughter in law against her mother in law; a man’s enemies are the men of his own house.
verses.verse_html: 6For the son dishonoureth the father, the daughter riseth up against her mother, the daughter in law against her mother in law; a man’s enemies are the men of his own house.

verses.text_plain: Therefore I will look unto the Lord; I will wait for the God of my salvation: my God will hear me.
verses.verse_html: 7Therefore I will look unto the Lord; I will wait for the God of my salvation: my God will hear me.

verses.text_plain: Rejoice not against me, O mine enemy: when I fall, I shall arise; when I sit in darkness, the Lord shall be a light unto me.
verses.verse_html: 8Rejoice not against me, O mine enemy: when I fall, I shall arise; when I sit in darkness, the Lord shall be a light unto me.

tokens.text: not against me, O mine enemy

verses.text_plain: I will bear the indignation of the Lord, because I have sinned against him, until he plead my cause, and execute judgment for me: he will bring me forth to the light, and I shall behold his righteousness.
verses.verse_html: 9I will bear the indignation of the Lord, because I have sinned against him, until he plead my cause, and execute judgment for me: he will bring me forth to the light, and I shall behold his righteousness.

tokens.text: for me: he will bring me forth

verses.text_plain: Then she that is mine enemy shall see it, and shame shall cover her which said unto me, Where is the Lord thy God? mine eyes shall behold her: now shall she be trodden down as the mire of the streets.
verses.verse_html:
10Then she that is mine enemy shall see it, and shame shall cover her which said unto me, Where is the Lord thy God? mine eyes shall behold her: now shall she be trodden down as the mire of the streets. ▼
▼ Then…: or, And thou wilt see her that is mine enemy, and cover her with shame
 , ▼
▼ shall she…: Heb. she shall be for a treading down

tokens.text: unto me, Where is the Lord
her: now shall she be trodden down

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Then…: or, And thou wilt see her that is mine enemy, and cover her with shame
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Then…: or, And thou wilt see her that is mine enemy, and cover her with shame

footnotes.body_text: ▼ shall she…: Heb. she shall be for a treading down
footnotes.body_html: ▼ shall she…: Heb. she shall be for a treading down

verses.text_plain: In the day that thy walls are to be built, in that day shall the decree be far removed.
verses.verse_html: 11In the day that thy walls are to be built, in that day shall the decree be far removed.

verses.text_plain: In that day also he shall come even to thee from Assyria, and from the fortified cities, and from the fortress even to the river, and from sea to sea, and from mountain to mountain.
verses.verse_html:
12In that day also he shall come even to thee from Assyria, and from the fortified cities, and from the fortress even to the river, and from sea to sea, and from mountain to mountain. ▼
▼ and from the fortified cities: or, even to the fortified cities

footnotes.body_text: ▼ and from the fortified cities: or, even to the fortified cities
footnotes.body_html: ▼ and from the fortified cities: or, even to the fortified cities

verses.text_plain: Notwithstanding the land shall be desolate because of them that dwell therein, for the fruit of their doings.
verses.verse_html:
13Notwithstanding the land shall be desolate because of them that dwell therein, for the fruit of their doings. ▼
▼ Notwithstanding: or, After that it hath been

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Notwithstanding: or, After that it hath been
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Notwithstanding: or, After that it hath been

verses.text_plain: Feed thy people with thy rod, the flock of thine heritage, which dwell solitarily in the wood, in the midst of Carmel: let them feed in Bashan and Gilead, as in the days of old.
verses.verse_html:
14Feed thy people with thy rod, the flock of thine heritage, which dwell solitarily in the wood, in the midst of Carmel: let them feed in Bashan and Gilead, as in the days of old. ▼
▼ Feed: or, Rule

verses.text_plain: According to the days of thy coming out of the land of Egypt will I shew unto him marvellous things.
verses.verse_html: 15According to the days of thy coming out of the land of Egypt will I shew unto him marvellous things.

verses.text_plain: The nations shall see and be confounded at all their might: they shall lay their hand upon their mouth, their ears shall be deaf.
verses.verse_html: 16The nations shall see and be confounded at all their might: they shall lay their hand upon their mouth, their ears shall be deaf.

verses.text_plain: They shall lick the dust like a serpent, they shall move out of their holes like worms of the earth: they shall be afraid of the Lord our God, and shall fear because of thee.
verses.verse_html:
17They shall lick the dust like a serpent, they shall move out of their holes like worms of the earth: they shall be afraid of the Lord our God, and shall fear because of thee. ▼
▼ worms: or, creeping things

footnotes.body_html: ▼ worms: or, creeping things

verses.text_plain: Who is a God like unto thee, that pardoneth iniquity, and passeth by the transgression of the remnant of his heritage? he retaineth not his anger for ever, because he delighteth in mercy.
verses.verse_html: 18Who is a God like unto thee, that pardoneth iniquity, and passeth by the transgression of the remnant of his heritage? he retaineth not his anger for ever, because he delighteth in mercy.

verses.text_plain: He will turn again, he will have compassion upon us; he will subdue our iniquities; and thou wilt cast all their sins into the depths of the sea.
verses.verse_html: 19He will turn again, he will have compassion upon us; he will subdue our iniquities; and thou wilt cast all their sins into the depths of the sea.

verses.text_plain: Thou wilt perform the truth to Jacob, and the mercy to Abraham, which thou hast sworn unto our fathers from the days of old.
verses.verse_html: 20Thou wilt perform the truth to Jacob, and the mercy to Abraham, which thou hast sworn unto our fathers from the days of old.
